Posted in Across The Land
the Awesome lady at Chic filA
Posted on May 1, 2016 | Leave a comment
mom and some of our family were eating in a restaurant last night and she (mom) noticed a lady wearing an alzheimers shirt. Mom initiated a conversation. It seems that Gleniss had an alzheimers connection either now, or in the past and had attended a Walk to End Alzheimers event.
This lady told mom that she wears the shirt in public so folks will think of alzheimers. She is raising awareness.
A lot of caregivers that attend a Walk, keep coming back, even after the loss of their friend or loved one. Thats pretty darn awesome!
