Posted in Across The Land
some things I have learned on this 47 monthjourney
Posted on May 1, 2016 | Leave a comment
Dont do anything fancy.
See the people, often, that you are trying to help, and always be accessible to them.
Be who you really are at all times. If strangers speak about you, and your close friends and family wonder who in the heck they are talking about, that might signal a problem.
I am not an ultra runner.
Its not a track and field event.
I am not a movie star.
I am a quiet man that gets nervous around a big group of people.
I care about caregivers.
I have family and friends that me.
I have family and friends that I need.
Sometimes I get tired.
I care about the fight with Alzheimers disease.
I respect the mission of the Alzheimers Association.
A lot of people have helped me in my life.
God is Great!
