Posted in Across The Land
running
Posted on April 30, 2016 | Leave a comment
It was a means to an end for me, at first. To reach the level of fitness I required for myself, I need aerobic exercise 4 to 5 times each week. I was tired of popping the CD in and turning on the television. Frankly, I was also disgusted with being inside.
My running was born from that.
Folks, that should know, tell me that good cardiovascular health slows, and in some cases even prevents disease.
Dr. Kenneth Cooper has been broadcasting that for years. I have a very healthy respect for Mr. Cooper.
I love running at a 12 minute per mile pace and breaking it up with walking and stopping to, so to speak, to smell the roses.
I do however continue to keep my heart rate at 75% of my maximum, for 30 minutes, 4 times a week. The low pace is what I am counting on to keep my musculoskeletal system in good enough shape to be able to run into my 90s. The aerobics hopefully, will help keep me healthy.
